I've been playing Angry Birds since the first release of the original game.   It's addicting. Luckily, I'm not a suggestible idiot or I may have spent money on the game(s).  That's quite an accomplishment.  Next month, on the 11th, will be my 11th anniversary for not giving you any money. 
Hey, the 11th on the 11th. Nice. 

1) Why do you require a connection to the internet?  
NOTHING about this game is live. Unless, everyone playing is willing to wait literally 10 days for me to fling a bird before they fling theirs. Highly unlikely. 

2) Why do you keep debuffing the birds?
The stronger they get, the less accuracy and breaking power.  Shouldn't they actually get better when they level up?  So, this is obviously a sorry attempt to squeeze cash out of suggestible people. 

3) Why have the birds become slower and jerkier?
This game takes very little space. There's no apparent reason why gameplay should become so retarded with each new update. 

All these questions lead to the last and most important:

4) Is Rovio spying on us?
I'm pretty sure that both Tencent and I already know the answer to that question.
